# The tools — WA Tool & Trusted Advisor

Two services turn pillars into a **score**.

## AWS Well-Architected Tool

- Define a **workload**; pick **lenses** — WA Framework (default) + Serverless, SaaS, FTR, ML, IoT, Analytics, Hybrid Net
- Unchecked options → **HRIs / MRIs**, scored per pillar
- Notes + tickets; **re-run every 6–12 months** → trend
- **Custom lenses** — encode org / regulated standards

## Trusted Advisor

- Five categories: **Cost · Performance · Security · Fault Tolerance · Service Limits**
- **Free tier** = 7 core checks (root MFA, public S3, exposed keys, limits); **Business/Enterprise** = full set
- Publishes to **EventBridge** (*new public bucket → alert*)

**Together:** WA Tool = periodic **workload** review · Trusted Advisor = continuous **account** monitoring.
